# 4. 天秤

Honami: We can't seem to reach a consensus...
Saki: Ugh, this is so hard! How are we supposed to choose between our solo show and the Fan Festival?
Shiho: Especially since either would be beneficial for us.
Shiho: It's important to constantly try to bring in new fans, but it's just as crucial to keep your existing ones happy.
Honami: Hey, everyone...
Honami: Just as a thought... If we set aside the benefit to the band, which would you all choose, just personally?
Ichika: Personally...
Ichika: In that case... I'm leaning towards the Fan Festival.
Shiho: Yeah, I had a feeling.
Ichika: Haha... Part of it is that the Fan Festival means a lot to me, since I've watched it for so long...
Ichika: But I also think it's a really good opportunity for us to get our music out there to a lot of new people.
Honami: Ichika...
Saki: But writing a song for the Fan Festival would mean that we can't do one for our solo show...
Shiho: Saki...
Saki: Ah, I'm sorry! I wasn't trying to argue!
Saki: It's just, it's our very first solo show as pros. I want to do everything we can for the people who have stuck with us this whole time.
Saki: That's why I think I'd prefer to focus on the solo show.
Shiho: If I had to pick one, yeah, I'd want to do the new song for the solo show too.
Shiho: You don't get too many chances to see people react to a brand-new song from up close, after all.
Ichika: Right...
Ichika: I mean... I also totally understand how you two feel. I still can't make up my mind.
Shiho: It's really not an easy comparison to make.
Honami: (Which is why this is such a difficult choice...)
Honami: (But if we don't decide soon...)
Honami: (We're already behind schedule for our solo show as it is, and if we want to write a new song for either event, we need to start soon.)
Honami: (Normally, I'd want to spend more time thinking about this. But...)
Honami: Everyone.
Honami: Would it be alright if I took control of this decision?
Shiho: Huh?
Honami: I realized something as we spoke... It seems that our own feelings matter just as much as the potential benefits to our band.
Honami: So, I feel that I should take a further look at this decision from other perspectives.
Honami: To find out which is truly in Leo/need's best interest.
Saki: In Leo/need's best interest...
Honami: *Nod* But if we all discuss every new piece of information, it's going to take a really long time to get anywhere.
Honami: So, I'd like to sift through and organize all the information available to us right now.
Honami: Then, after that, I'll have us all meet back up to make our final decision.
Ichika: Honami...
Shiho: But won't that be a ton of work for you?
Honami: It'll be okay. While I do that, I'd like to leave our setlist and the effects we'll use to you three.
Honami: In the end... Just as Mr. Shindo said, this is a question of the principles we want to follow as a band.
Honami: So, while I do want us to be able to sit down and discuss until everyone is satisfied... I want to make our general direction clear.
Honami: As the leader of Leo/need.
Saki: Hona...
Shiho: Okay.
Shiho: While you think about that, we'll continue preparing for our solo show.
Ichika: Yeah... But don't push yourself too hard, okay?
Ichika: Please let us know if you need our help.
Honami: Thank you, I will.
Honami: Let's do our best in the end to reach a decision that makes us all happy.
Honami: (I am a little worried about this, but I need to do my best here.)
Honami: (To figure out what the best choice is for Leo/need.)
